article_title: Warplane crashes near Damascus, causes unclear: Syrian Observatory for Human Rights
article_text:
The plane crashed southeast of Damascus airport, the British-based monitoring group said, after flying over territory controlled by Islamic State. The fate of the pilot was not known.

Islamic State earlier said a Syrian warplane had been shot down. Its statement could not be independently verified.

(This version of the story was corrected to say plane crashed southeast of airport)

(Reporting by John Davison; Editing by Hugh Lawson)
